contentbylabel macro has 'label' as a required parameter; however you can leave out the key word 'label' and just specify the list of label values. 

{code}
{contentbylabel:goodpage}
{code}

You can also include/exclude matches by using +/- before the label values.

{code}
{contentbylabel:label=+goodpage,-badpage}
{code}


However, these do not work at the same time; the following will give 'No content found for label(s) +goodpage':


{code}
{contentbylabel:+goodpage}
{code}

If the following snippet is used:

{code}
{panel:title=General Description of the Service|borderStyle=none|bgColor=99ff33}
test
{panel}
{code}

It will generate a nice green background in the Rich Text Editor, and Preview.  If you save, and view the actual result, it's a gray box.  Understandably, the tag should have a hash sign before the color hex value.  This would fix the problem.  But this is afflicting users who are upgrading Confluence where this tag style worked fine, and are only encountering it after upgrading.  We should make the behavior consistent across the RTE, Preview, and View.

